# A Simple Explanation of SEO and PPC (And Which One to Use)

To expand your website’s reach, you need to increase its visibility. One of the best ways is to make sure prospects find it when they search for your business.

You can do this two ways.

## Option 1: Search Engine Optimization (SEO).

Your first option to increase your website’s visibility is to use Search Engine Optimization, abbreviated as SEO. This simply means finetuning your website so search engines like Google will recognize it as relevant to people who are searching for your business. At the most basic form, this requires two things:

1. You must embed a quality description and list of keywords. These are hidden from people who visit your website, but they help the search engine identify who is interested in your website.  
2. When building your website, you must use quality titles and include content relevant to your prospects.

Although you can use more advanced methods, this is the most basic approach to SEO. By finetuning your website, you can help raise your website’s visibility when people search for your business.

SEO is an attractive option because it allows you to rank organically on Google. It is often a great approach for local, non-competitive niches. However, if you are in a competitive niche, you may face these challenges:

1. It takes time to increase your ranking. If a competitor has gained a head start on their SEO, it may take months, sometimes even years, to catch up to their rank.

2. You never have ultimate control. Google is constantly tweaking their search algorithm. This means that you might be the first search result for a certain term, but could drop off the first page when they update their search algorithm.

## Option 2: Pay per Click Advertising (PPC)

Your second option is using paid advertisements to promote your website. You determine the keywords that are relevant to you, bid on those keywords. Based on your bid price and relevancy, Google determines your ad’s position. However, you are only charged when someone actually clicks on your website.

Why choose to pay for a Google listing instead of relying on the free SEO?

**Reason 1: It increases your visibility.** Even if you rank as the first organic search, you may still appear beneath 4 of your competitors’ paid ad listings. As people continue moving to mobile devices, it’s becoming increasingly important to appear near the top of the results.

**Reason 2: You become Google’s customer**. Almost all of Google’s revenue comes from advertising, and they have a vested interest in helping advertisers. 

**Reason 3: You can get immediate results**. You don’t have to wait to climb up the Google page ranks. You can set up your ad and start getting clicks the same day.

**Reason 4: It puts you back in control.** You get to control when and where your ad is displayed based on the ad’s schedule, targeting, and bid price. It’s true that you might be subject to prices rising. However, your competitors face these same price changes as well.

While Pay per Click advertising is not a profitable move for every business, it can give certain businesses the level of control they need in order to bring in new customers.

## Which One to Use

When choosing between SEO and PPC, you should ask yourself these questions:

1. **How much can I afford to spend to get a new customer?** Rather than merely looking at lowering advertising costs, consider looking at ways to increase the lifetime value of a customer.

2. **How important are these customers to my business?** If you’re not relying on traffic from your website and can afford waiting for search engine ranking, it may be the best option for you. However, if new customers are crucial to your business, you need a strategy that puts you in control of the outcome.
